BEIJING, Nov. 18 (Xinhua) -- Domestic comedy-suspense film "Be Somebody" remained atop the Chinese mainland box office chart on Wednesday, figures from the China Movie Data Information Network showed Thursday. The film, which follows a group of frustrated filmmakers who gather to plan on a new film about a notorious criminal case, raked in 22.75 million yuan (3.57 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday, its seventh day of screening. It was followed by "Anita," a biopic that recounts the life story of legendary Hong Kong singer and actress Anita Mui. The film netted over 5.84 million yuan on its sixth day of screening. War epic film "The Battle at Lake Changjin" ranked third with a daily revenue of 3.24 million yuan, raising its total box office to around 5.64 billion yuan 49 days after its debut. Enditem